  '<p><code>inspectMustStaple(rawDer)</code> walks the X.509 cert DER and reads the RFC 7633 TLS Feature extension (OID <code>1.3.6.1.5.5.7.1.24</code>). Returns <code>{ mustStaple, features }</code> where <code>mustStaple === true</code> when status_request (5) is in the feature list. A cert advertising must-staple is contractually required to ship an OCSP staple on every connection — connections without a staple MUST be refused per RFC 7633 §4.2.3. <code>requireMustStaple(opts)</code> returns a <code>(peerCert, ctx) → Error|null</code> predicate that refuses connections where the cert demands a staple but none was delivered. Pass <code>enforceUnconditional: true</code> to also refuse staple-less responses on certs that don\'t carry must-staple — operator-stricter-than-RFC posture.</p>',
